{"lemma":"سَمٌّ","slug":"سَمٌّ","root":"س.م.م","root_slug":"س-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/س-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَمّ","root":"سمم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20593"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to poison (someone, something)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"poison, toxin"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"venom"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَمَّ (samma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"opening, hole"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"eye (of a needle)","examples":[{"text":"إِنَّ ٱلَّذِينَ كَذَّبُوا بِآيَاتِنَا وَٱسْتَكْبَرُوا عَنْهَا لَا تُفَتَّحُ لَهُمْ أَبْوَابُ ٱلسَّمَاءِ وَلَا يَدْخُلُونَ ٱلْجَنَّةَ حَتَّى يَلِجَ ٱلْجَمَلُ فِي سَمِّ ٱلْخِيَاطِ","english":"Indeed, those who deny Our verses and are arrogant toward them: the gates of Heaven will not be opened for them, nor will they enter Paradise until a camel enters into the eye of a needle."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew סַם."},"ipa":["/sam.ma/","/samm/","/summ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20593","headword_ar":"سَمٌّ","root":"sm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Poison,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vemom;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(PS, TK;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deadly poison"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"venom;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poison,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"venom, of the serpent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain deadly thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~N","text_ar":"سُمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) which is of the dial. of the people of El-'Áliyeh, (Yoo, Msb, TA,) and is said to be the most chaste; (MF, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sim~N","text_ar":"سِمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) which is [said to be] of the dial. of Temeem, (Msb,) [but is thought by SM to be vulgar, and] accord. to Yoo, the first is of the dial. of Temeem, (TA,) and this is the most common of the three: (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simaAmN","text_ar":"سِمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwmN","text_ar":"سُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samosamN","text_ar":"سَمْسَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, in the sing. sense. (ISk, K, TA.) [In some copies of the K, by a mistranscription ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAls~am~i","text_ar":"وَالسَّمِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAls~um~i","text_ar":"وَالسُّمِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wAls~am~u","text_ar":"والسَّمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAls~um~u","text_ar":"وَالسُّمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~N","text_ar":"سَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~N","text_ar":"سُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made to be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samosamN","text_ar":"سَمْسَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “ a fox. ” That the right reading is that which I have followed is shown in the TA by an ex., in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samosam","text_ar":"سَمْسَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is spoken of as drunk.] ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~u AlfaA^ori","text_ar":"سَمُّ الفَاْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Arsenic;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in like manner called by us"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ratsbane;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ak~u","text_ar":"الشَّكُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ahaju","text_ar":"الرَّهَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is a modern word for arsenic]. (TA.) [Also applied in the present day to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hyoscyamus muticus"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn. (Delile's Floræ Aegypt. Illustr., in the Descr. de l'Égypte, no. 242.)] ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~u AlHimaAri","text_ar":"سَمُّ الحِمَارِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difolaY","text_ar":"دِفْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~u Als~amaki","text_ar":"سَمُّ السَّمَكِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tree called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAhiyzahoraho","text_ar":"مَاهِيزَهْرَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAhiY zahoraho","text_ar":"مَاهِى زَهْرَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K,) which latter appellation is Pers., meaning the same, [i. e. “ fish-poison, ”] (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and also known by the name of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbuwSiyru","text_ar":"البُوصِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is beneficial for pains of the joints, and pain of the hip and the back, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqoris","text_ar":"نِقْرِس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gout,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or specially"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gout in the foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feet"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but the only part of its tree that is beneficial is its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liHaA='","text_ar":"لِحَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bark"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when somewhat thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kneaded mith leaven,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is put into a pool of water, it intoxicates the fish thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that they float upon the surface of the water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and its leaves burn in lamps in lieu of wicks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of their oleaginous property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~u A^aboraSa","text_ar":"سَمُّ اَبْرَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAm~N","text_ar":"سَامٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~N","text_ar":"سُمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sim~N","text_ar":"سِمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) [but the last is thought by SM to be vulgar, in this sense as well as in the first,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A perforation, bore,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K,) of anything; (M;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is narrow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) for instance, (S, TA,) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a needle; (S, Msb, TA;) as in the Kur vii. 38; [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jum~alN","text_ar":"جُمَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hole"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the nose, and of the ear: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwmN","text_ar":"سُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simaAmN","text_ar":"سِمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or both. (S, K.) The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwm","text_ar":"سُمُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simaAm","text_ar":"سِمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a human being are His"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mouth and"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nostril and"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mouth and"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nostrils and"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) and the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~N","text_ar":"سَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~N","text_ar":"سُمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwm","text_ar":"سُمُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a human being, and of a horse or the like, are the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clefts"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAq~","text_ar":"مَشَاقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":") of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (M.) And the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwm","text_ar":"سُمُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse are The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thin portions of the hard bone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the two sides of the nasal bone to the channels of the tears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~N","text_ar":"سَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or, as some say, (M,) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~aAni","text_ar":"سَمَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~","text_ar":"سَمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, [but this seems evidently to be a mistake for the dual,]) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two veins in the nose"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anof","text_ar":"اَنْف"},{"kind":"text","text":", M, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayo$uwm","text_ar":"خَيْشُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, K, [which latter often means the same as the former,]) of the horse: (S, M, K:) accord. to Lth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwmN","text_ar":"سُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~N","text_ar":"سَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channels of the tears"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse: AO says that in the face of the horse are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwm","text_ar":"سُمُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the bareness of his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwm","text_ar":"سُمُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is approved, and is regarded as indicative of generous breed. (TA.) By the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwm","text_ar":"سُمُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse are also meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any bone"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bones"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is marrow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwm","text_ar":"سُمُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a sword are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Notches"},{"kind":"text","text":"therein, whether new or old. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAba sam~a","text_ar":"اَصَابَ سَمَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjatihi","text_ar":"حَاجَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is app. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~N","text_ar":"سَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying the “ eye ” of a needle, or the like, and] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attained, the object of his aim"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pursuit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa baSiyrN bisam~i HaAjatihi","text_ar":"هُوَ بَصِيرٌ بِسَمِّ حَاجَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skilful, in respect of the object of his aim"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pursuit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b3-  [And hence, perhaps, though another derivation is asserted in what follows,] one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlahu sam~N walaA Ham~N gayoruka","text_ar":"مَالَهُ سَمٌّ وَلَا حَمٌّ غَيْرُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA Hum~N","text_ar":"وَلَا حُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~N","text_ar":"سُمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has no object in his mind except thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ham~N","text_ar":"هَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlahu sam~N walaA Ham~N","text_ar":"مَالَهُ سَمٌّ وَلَا حَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA","text_ar":"وَلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~N","text_ar":"سُمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~N","text_ar":"حُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[alone]: or, accord. to Fr, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he has not any who hopes for him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is from ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samamotu","text_ar":"سَمَمْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~aka","text_ar":"سَمَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamamotu Ham~aka","text_ar":"حَمَمْتُ حَمَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hamamotu ham~aka","text_ar":"هَمَمْتُ هَمَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSadotu qaSodaka","text_ar":"قَصَدْتُ قَصْدَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~N","text_ar":"سَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ham~N","text_ar":"حَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the inf. ns., and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~N","text_ar":"سُمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~N","text_ar":"حُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the simple substs.; and the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he has not any who seeks after him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he has no good in him for which he is to be sought after:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Meyd:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he has neither little nor much."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hm","text_ar":"حم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~N","text_ar":"سَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loop"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eurowap","text_ar":"عُرْوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":") of the [girth called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDiyn","text_ar":"وَضِين"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwmN","text_ar":"سُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musam~amN","text_ar":"مُسَمَّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadaE","text_ar":"وَدَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cowries"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought forth from the sea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and strung for ornament."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And also, (TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~N","text_ar":"سُمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~apN","text_ar":"سُمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strung"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadaE","text_ar":"وَدَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cowries"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwmN","text_ar":"سُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","Yoo","TA","Meyd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}